Useful information
Definitions
Climate Change Levy (CCL)
This is a government energy tax on industrial and commercial consumption. If applicable, the tax is calculated at the CCL rate on the front of this invoice. Please visit hmrc.gov.uk for
further information on CCL.
The De Minimis rule
If a premises uses an average of less than 33 kWh a day (approx. 1,000 kWh a month), it is deemed as 'Domestic' for that month and attracts the domestic rate for VAT. CCL will not be
charged for that period.
Company information
Orsted Sales (UK) Ltd is an agent of Orsted Power Sales (UK) Ltd. Our full company registration details are shown at the bottom of your invoice.
How to pay your invoice
By Direct Debit your balance will be collected automatically on the specified due date. Complete a Direct Debit form at orsted.co.uk/info-hub/handy-documents.
By bank transfer to the details below, quoting your account reference number:
Bank: Nordea Bank AB
Account number: 46433601
Sort code: 40-48-78
IBAN: GB85 NDEA 4048 7846 4336 01
SWIFT code: NDEAGB2L
By credit or debit card online at orstedportal.co.uk or by calling 0800 056 8101.
By cheque made payable to Orsted Sales (UK) Ltd, quoting your company name and account reference number on the back.
If you have any problems with payment, please contact our Customer Services team using the contact details on the front page of this invoice.
If you're moving premises
If you're moving, it's important that you let us know. You can complete a 'Change of tenancy' form at orsted.co.uk/info-hub/handy-documents. Please send the completed form to
customer_transfers@orsted.co.uk.
If you're unhappy with our service
We're passionate about giving you the very best service. If you have any sort of issue, the best thing to do is contact us and we'll do everything we can to help. Our complaints process
can be found on our website at orsted.co.uk/our-service-pledge. If you feel we haven't dealt with your complaint as you would have liked, you can also contact Citizens Advice Bureau on
0845 404 0506 for free, impartial advice.
In the event of a power cut
To report a power cut, call the national power emergency service on 105. This is a 24-hour emergency line.
Alternatively, you can contact your local Distribution Network Operator (DNO) using the details below.
